  "text": "level location mentioned. When multiple locations were mentioned, the tweet was assigned all the locations mentioned. If there was no location information, the tweet was removed from the sample. After completing this preprocessing, 31 million English and 41 million Arabic tweets were used to compute buzz and sentiment variables at the district and governorate levels. Our team also has access to an unstructured archive of over 700 million articles [CITATION_1] . We use a subset of more than 1.4 million English-language articles that either contained the name of a location in Iraq or were from a news source in Iraq. The buzz variables generated from these newspaper data are at the country spatial granularity.",
